4 Published CMIP7 BC_em_AIR_anthro False published A bug was found in gridding of data for that led to spurious emissions for CO, CO2, and NOx, for the industrial (IND) and energy (ENE) sectors. These spurious emissions span 1961 - 2021. Globally, the differences represent less than 0.001% of annual emissions, but sometimes individual grid cell changes can sometimes represent a factor of 2 change (for small emissions). CEDS-CMIP-2025-03-18 Rachel Hoesly (rachel.hoesly@pnnl.gov); Steve Smith (ssmith@pnnl.gov) 10.5281/zenodo.15001544 emissions mon https://www.pnnl.gov/projects/ceds gn PNNL-JGCRI CC BY 4.0 atmos 2025-03-18 CMIP 175001-202312

These spurious emissions span 1961 - 2021. Globally, the differences represent less than 0.001% of annual emissions, but sometimes individual grid cell changes can sometimes represent a factor of 2 change (for small emissions). 789 Published CMIP7 NMVOC_em_AIR_anthro False published A bug was found in gridding of data for that led to spurious emissions for CO, CO2, and NOx, for the industrial (IND) and energy (ENE) sectors. These spurious emissions span 1961 - 2021. Globally, the differences represent less than 0.001% of annual emissions, but sometimes individual grid cell changes can sometimes represent a factor of 2 change (for small emissions). Globally, the differences represent less than 0.001% of annual emissions, but sometimes individual grid cell changes can sometimes represent a factor of 2 change (for small emissions). 1758 Published CMIP7 pop_dens True published These datasets used an old version of WorldPop/FuturePop data. PIK-CMIP-1-0-1 uses revised WorldPop/FuturePop data hence supercedes PIK-CMIP-1-0-0. If you have started historical simulations based on `PIK-CMIP-1-0-0`, please restart and use the updated files. Note that even for PIK-CMIP-1-0-1, HYDE 3.2 is still used as newer data were not obtained. PIK-CMIP-1-0-1 also includes a fix to a bug discovered in the 0.25 degree resolution files in PIK-CMIP-1-0-0 thanks to @slm7826 and @vnaik60 (see #362). The 0.5 degree data was not affected by this bug.
